		<info>
			<li>WT Col-0 and mutant plants were grown for 28 days in continuous light (at the University of Minnesota) or a 16/8 h light/dark cycle at the Noble Foundation (Oklahoma), under perforated metal sheets such that leaves could be rapidly harvested with a razor blade</li>
			<li>Trichomes were dislodged by vortexing with small glass beads 60-80 mm in diameter in 1x PBS   in the presence of 50 mM EGTA, and were retrieved with a 100 mm cell strainer</li>
			<li>RNA was isolated from approximately 100 mg of trichomes (wet weight) stored in RNAlater, and hybridized to the ATH1 chip in duplicate-quintuplicate: the average signal is shown</li>
			<li>Data normalized by GCOS/MAS5, TGT 100</li>
			<li>Marks et al. (2009) Mol. Plant 2: 803-22; Gilding and Marks (2010) Plant J. 64:304-17.</li>
		</info>
